article.headline: Santa Clara 79, Loyola Marymount 56
article.story: SANTA CLARA, Calif. -- Marc Trasolini scored 26 points in his final home game, and Santa Clara rolled to a 79-56 victory Thursday night over free-falling Loyola Marymount. Trasolini was 9 of 12 from the floor. Fellow seniors Kevin Foster and Raymond Cowels scored 17 and 12, respectively, for the Broncos (21-9, 9-6 West Coast), and all five of Santa Clara's seniors were honored before the game. Santa Clara shot 51 percent from the floor and made nine 3-pointers. The Broncos never trailed and led by as many as 29. Anthony Ireland had 23 points for the Lions (8-21, 1-14), who lost their 13th in a row. Alex Osborne scored a career-high 15 points and grabbed 10 rebounds. Both teams finish the regular season Saturday: Santa Clara at Saint Mary's, and Loyola Marymount hosting BYU. Santa Clara probably will be the No. 4 seed in the WCC tournament, while Loyola will be No. 9.
